fields.title: MONKFROG
fields.description:
MONKFROG is a production-ready, full-stack e-commerce application designed to sell themed merchandise. I architected this solution to simulate a real-world shopping environment, focusing on secure data handling, performance optimization, and a polished user experience. It bridges a high-performance React frontend with a scalable Django Rest Framework backend.

1.Authentication:JWT (JSON Web Tokens)
2.Services:SendGrid (Email Automation), WhiteNoise (Static Files)
3.Deployment: Vercel (Frontend), Render (Backend)

fields.title: Smart Access Hub for Urban Mobility
fields.description:
Smart Access Hub for Urban Mobility is basically the city's glow-up in app form â€” one smooth platform where citizens can book events, reserve public facilities, check parking in real time, and use one secure Universal QR Code for everything. Behind the scenes, admins get a powerful Command Center with live dashboards, instant stats, and a built-in AI assistant, CityBot, that answers questions using actual database insights. It cuts out the chaos of disconnected systems and makes the whole urban experience way more fluid, smart, and efficient.

ðŸ’ Key Highlights

1.AI Assistant (CityBot): Powered by Google Gemini 2.0, offering voice-based, context-aware guidance using live data.
2.Live Operations Dashboard: Auto-updating every 5 seconds to track traffic, capacity, and usage trends.
3.RBAC Security: Tight JWT-based access separation for citizens and administrators.
4.Unified QR System: Encrypted passes used across events, facilities, and parking for smooth entry validation.
5.Centralized City Services: Bookings, reservations, and real-time monitoring all in one place.

fields.title: Automated CI/CD Pipeline on AWS Tech Stack
fields.description:
The project delivers a fully automated DevOps pipeline where every push to GitHub instantly rolls into a fresh Docker image and ships straight to an AWS EC2 server â€” no manual touching, no late-night config panic. Jenkins sits at the heart of the setup, orchestrating builds, tests, and deployments through Webhook triggers. The result? A deployment flow thatâ€™s fast, consistent, and eliminates nearly all operational overhead while keeping the Django app running like a champ.

2.Containerization: Packaged the Django project into a Docker image for smooth, environment-independent releases.

fields.content:
## How Iâ€™m Building My Full-Stack & DevOps Portfolio From Scratch â€” And What Iâ€™m Learning Along the Way 

Every developer has that one project that becomes more than just a project.  
For me, itâ€™s my portfolio.

I didnâ€™t want a basic â€œHi, Iâ€™m Xâ€ website with two buttons and a list of skills.  
I wanted something that actually *represents* who I am:

- A full-stack developer who builds things  
- A DevOps enthusiast who deploys things  
- A problem solver who loves systems, automation, and clean engineering

So I started building my portfolio from scratch â€” **as a real, end-to-end full-stack + DevOps product.**  
And honestlyâ€¦ itâ€™s been one of the most exciting builds of my life.

---

## The Goal: A Portfolio That Doesnâ€™t Just Show My Skills â€” It *Runs* Them

I didnâ€™t want a static website.  
I wanted a **living system**.

Something that:

- tracks who visits  
- shows real-time analytics  
- has an admin dashboard  
- stores files like a mini cloud drive  
- includes a blogging system  
- uses modern animations and 3D elements  
- looks clean on every screen  
- and feels like a product, not a resume

---

##The Tech I Chose (And Why)

### **Frontend â€” React + Tailwind + Framer Motion**
Because I wanted:

- smooth animations  
- clean components  
- responsiveness  
- full control over UI  

React gives me that superpower.

---

### **Backend â€” Django + DRF + PostgreSQL**
I needed something:

- stable  
- secure  
- scalable  
- perfect for analytics + dashboard + blogging  

Django is a beast for this.

---

### **DevOps â€” Docker, Nginx, CI/CD**
This is the part I enjoy the most.

I wanted my portfolio to actually show my DevOps side:

- containerized services  
- automatic deployment  
- reverse proxy  
- proper HTTPS  
- logs + uptime monitoring  

Basicallyâ€¦ a mini production-grade deployment.

---

## The Coolest Part: The Visitor Analytics System

Most portfolios donâ€™t even know if someone opens the page.

Mine?

- Tracks every unique visitor  
- Logs every page they visit  
- Shows real-time active users  
- Displays geo-location  
- Has a full dashboard where *I* can view everything  

Itâ€™s my own tiny version of Google Analytics â€” built by me.

---

## The Admin Dashboard I Always Wanted

Inside my hidden admin panel, I can:

- manage projects  
- manage certifications  
- upload and download files  
- write and publish blogs  
- check analytics  
- control content  
- view system health  

It feels like logging into my own startup.

---

## The Feature That Makes Everyone Go â€œWOWâ€

### **AI-powered personal assistant.**  
A chatbot trained on **my portfolio**, **my projects**, and **my skills**.

Visitors can ask:

- â€œWhat has he built?â€  
- â€œExplain his EMS project.â€  
- â€œWhat DevOps tools does he know?â€  
- â€œShow me his certifications.â€  

And the bot answers â€” like an interactive resume.

This one feature alone took the portfolio from â€œcoolâ€ â†’ **â€œbro what is this masterpiece??â€**

---

## What Iâ€™ve Learned Building This

### ðŸ”¸ Full-stack is fun  
But *full-stack + DevOps* is a different level of satisfaction.

### ðŸ”¸ Deployment is not the end â€” monitoring is  
Seeing your own dashboard update with live visitors is magical.

### ðŸ”¸ UI matters  
Even a simple animation can make the whole site feel premium.

### ðŸ”¸ Building something for yourself hits different  
This portfolio taught me more than many courses combined.

---

## Whatâ€™s Next?

Iâ€™m not done.  
Iâ€™m still adding:

- better 3D elements  
- more blogs  
- performance optimizations  
- new admin tools  
- and maybe a â€œguest modeâ€ for friends to test features  

This portfolio will grow with me.

Itâ€™s not just a website.  
Itâ€™s my **developer identity** â€” engineered from scratch.

---

## Final Thought

but something that evolves with your journey.

It will teach you:
